.TH "lpfc_check_pci_resettable" 9 "lpfc_check_pci_resettable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_check_pci_resettable \- Walks list of devices on pci_dev's bus to check if issuing a pci_bus_reset is possibly unsafe
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfc_check_pci_resettable
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
lpfc_hba pointer.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Walks the bus_list to ensure only PCI devices with Emulex
vendor id, device ids that support hot reset, and only one occurrence
of function 0.
.SH "RETURN"
-EBADSLT,  detected invalid device
0,    successful
